@page "/pricing"
@layout Meridian.Portal.Components.Layout.MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>Pricing · Meridian</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description"
          content="Meridian pricing scales with your pursuit pipeline. Three tiers, transparent volume, no per-seat tax." />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Pricing · Meridian" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Three tiers, scaled to your pursuit pipeline." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="mkt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Pricing</span>
        <h1>Priced against the pursuits you'd otherwise miss.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
            Volume-based, not per-seat. The whole BD team can use Meridian — what you pay for is
            the size of the pipeline it's watching for you.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="tiers mkt-section mkt-section-tight">
    <div class="mkt-container">
        <div class="tier-grid">
            <article class="tier">
                <header>
                    <h2>Starter</h2>
                    <p>Single-source ingestion. For teams testing the workflow before committing.</p>
                </header>
                <div class="tier-price"><span class="amount">Contact</span><span class="cadence">/ month</span></div>
                <ul class="tier-features">
                    <li>One ingestion source</li>
                    <li>Eight-dimension scoring</li>
                    <li>Single-step outreach</li>
                    <li>One CRM connection</li>
                    <li>500 outbound sends / month</li>
                </ul>
                <a class="mkt-btn mkt-btn-secondary mkt-btn-lg" href="mailto:hello@meridianbd.dev?subject=Meridian%20Starter">Talk to us</a>
            </article>

            <article class="tier tier-featured">
                <header>
                    <span class="tier-flag">Most teams pick this</span>
                    <h2>Pursuit</h2>
                    <p>The full pipeline. Multi-source, multi-step sequences, full CRM sync.</p>
                </header>
                <div class="tier-price"><span class="amount">Contact</span><span class="cadence">/ month</span></div>
                <ul class="tier-features">
                    <li>Unlimited ingestion sources</li>
                    <li>Eight-dimension scoring + tuning</li>
                    <li>Multi-step outreach sequences</li>
                    <li>All three CRM adapters</li>
                    <li>Daily caps and per-source throttles</li>
                    <li>Reply detection (incl. OOO routing)</li>
                </ul>
                <a class="mkt-btn mkt-btn-primary mkt-btn-lg" href="mailto:hello@meridianbd.dev?subject=Meridian%20Pursuit">Get a demo</a>
            </article>

            <article class="tier">
                <header>
                    <h2>Enterprise</h2>
                    <p>SSO, custom adapters, isolated infrastructure. For primes with compliance teams.</p>
                </header>
                <div class="tier-price"><span class="amount">Custom</span><span class="cadence">/ year</span></div>
                <ul class="tier-features">
                    <li>OIDC SSO (Okta, Entra, Auth0)</li>
                    <li>Custom source adapters</li>
                    <li>Dedicated infrastructure option</li>
                    <li>SLA + named support</li>
                    <li>Data-residency controls</li>
                </ul>
                <a class="mkt-btn mkt-btn-secondary mkt-btn-lg" href="mailto:hello@meridianbd.dev?subject=Meridian%20Enterprise">Talk to sales</a>
            </article>
        </div>

        <div class="price-rationale">
            <h3>Why we don't list a per-seat price.</h3>
            <p>
                BD teams have wildly different shapes. A two-person shop with a tight pipeline
                pays the same as a ten-person team with the same volume. The thing that scales
                Meridian's cost is the breadth of sources and the volume of outbound — so that's
                what scales the price. We'd rather quote you something honest than post a number
                that doesn't match what you'll actually use.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="faq mkt-section mkt-section-tight">
    <div class="mkt-container">
        <div class="section-head">
            <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
            <h2>Common questions before the demo call.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
            <details>
                <summary>Do I have to switch email providers?</summary>
                <p>No. Meridian sends through your existing Resend or Postmark account using a
                domain you already own. We never store your credentials in plaintext, and you
                can revoke access in one click.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Which CRMs do you support?</summary>
                <p>Pipedrive, HubSpot, and Salesforce out of the box. Custom integrations available
                on Enterprise.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>How is scoring different from "AI scoring"?</summary>
                <p>Every dimension is a deterministic function of structured fields you can inspect —
                NAICS match, set-aside fit, dollar band, geographic proximity, agency history,
                contracting officer activity, response window, and competition signal. No LLM
                in the scoring path. You can defend the score to anyone.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>What happens to opportunities we already track elsewhere?</summary>
                <p>If they're in one of the sources you connect, Meridian normalizes them and
                writes back to your CRM. If they're net-new pursuits we found and you don't want
                them, you can dismiss in one click and the scoring learns from the dismissals.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Can I see a real workspace before signing anything?</summary>
                <p>Yes — that's what "Get a demo" gets you. We'll set up a sandbox tenant with
                your sources and walk through the scoring with your team on a screen-share.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .mkt h2 { font-size: 36px; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.025em; font-weight: 650; }
    .mkt h3 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.015em; }
    .mkt-section.mkt-section-tight { padding: 72px 0; }
    .tier-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 56px;
    }
    .tier {
        padding: 48px 28px 32px;
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 24px;
        position: relative;
    }
    .tier-featured {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--accent-tint) 0%, var(--surface) 50%);
        border-color: var(--accent-soft);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    }
    .tier-flag {
        position: absolute;
        top: 22px;
        left: 28px;
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--accent);
    }
    .tier header h2 {
        font-size: 22px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .tier header p {
        font-size: 14.5px;
        color: var(--ink-2);
        margin: 0;
        line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .tier-price {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        display: flex;
        align-items: baseline;
        gap: 6px;
    }
    .tier-price .amount {
        font-family: var(--font);
        font-size: 30px;
        font-weight: 650;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        color: var(--ink);
    }
    .tier-price .cadence { color: var(--ink-3); font-size: 13.5px; }
    .tier-features {
        list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;
        display: grid; gap: 8px;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--ink-2);
    }
    .tier-features li {
        padding-left: 22px;
        position: relative;
    }
    .tier-features li::before {
        content: "✓";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 700;
    }
    .tier .mkt-btn { margin-top: auto; align-self: stretch; }
    .price-rationale {
        max-width: 720px;
        padding: 32px;
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        background: var(--paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    .price-rationale h3 { margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .price-rationale p { margin: 0; color: var(--ink-2); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; }

    .faq-list { display: grid; gap: 4px; max-width: 820px; }
    .faq-list details {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 18px 0;
    }
    .faq-list details:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .faq-list summary {
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 16px;
        cursor: pointer;
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
    }
    .faq-list summary::after {
        content: "+";
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        color: var(--ink-3);
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 20px;
    }
    .faq-list details[open] summary::after { content: "−"; }
    .faq-list summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .faq-list p {
        margin: 14px 0 0;
        color: var(--ink-2);
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        max-width: 720px;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 960px) {
        .tier-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>
